<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="202" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,863,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1044,1070]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe along all or part of its extension, when incomplete remaining part smoky black and narrow. Anterolateral margin not punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with black punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[814,918,1116,1142]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 19E</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin with a thin light-yellow line (
<figureCitation box="[353,455,1152,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 19E</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[874,973,1152,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 19F</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1296,1152,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,578,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-193@16.[151,1436,561,1949]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hypoxys nigrosinuatus sp. n.A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 9A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore dorsal rim with a pair of medial black rounded expansions (
<figureCitation box="[817,907,1188,1214]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,578,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-193@16.[151,1436,561,1949]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hypoxys nigrosinuatus sp. n.A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup oblique, long, broad, thick, and rugose; adjacent to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[946,1069,1224,1250]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,578,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-193@16.[151,1436,561,1949]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hypoxys nigrosinuatus sp. n.A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 9A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere remiform, short, dorsal margin acuminated medially; anterior and posterior angles triangular; stalk with inner margin carinated, carina curved anteriorly and evanescent distally (
<figureCitation box="[620,741,1296,1322]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,578,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-193@16.[151,1436,561,1949]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hypoxys nigrosinuatus sp. n.A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 9B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral tufts of setae separated by median glabrous bridge; posterior face pentagonal with a medial ridge (
<figureCitation box="[869,993,1332,1358]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,578,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-193@16.[151,1436,561,1949]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hypoxys nigrosinuatus sp. n.A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 9A–C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions rounded, small, slightly surpassing levels of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[966,1056,1368,1394]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,578,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-193@16.[151,1436,561,1949]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hypoxys nigrosinuatus sp. n.A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="202" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,863,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1404,1430]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Comments.</emphasis>
This specie is unique due to the shape of the superior process of the genital cup and paramere short (
<figureCitation box="[159,281,1440,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,578,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-193@16.[151,1436,561,1949]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Hypoxys nigrosinuatus sp. n.A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Fig. 9B–C</figureCitation>
). The paramere is somehow comparable with that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[871,1075,1440,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsocarinatus">
<emphasis box="[871,1075,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. dorsocarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1088,1275,1441,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrosinuatus">
<emphasis box="[1088,1275,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. nigrosinuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1907" box="[1289,1437,1440,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="offuscatus">
<emphasis box="[1289,1437,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. offuscatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1803" box="[199,359,1476,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridens">
<emphasis box="[199,359,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. quadridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see comments of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[570,775,1476,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsocarinatus">
<emphasis box="[570,775,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">H. dorsocarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1090,1512,1539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,863,1575]" box="[199,1090,1512,1539]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1512,1538]" pageId="15" pageNumber="202">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the black rounded mesial projections on dorsal rim.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
